In a 2-1/2-qt. microwave-safe dish, combine the onion and oil. Cover and microwave on high for 3 minutes. Stir in green onions and celery; cover and cook 3 minutes longer. Add potatoes, salt, Cajun seasoning and pepper. Cover and cook for 12 minutes or until potatoes are nearly tender. Stir in the shrimp and bacon. Cover and cook on high for 5 minutes or until shrimp is pink and potatoes are tender.